
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-grow-bgp-med-considerations-05.txt'>
    <title>"BGP MULTI_EXIT_DISC (MED) Considerations", Danny McPherson, Vijay Gill</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-grow-bgp-med-considerations-05.txt</link>
    <description>The BGP MULTI_EXIT_DISC (MED) attribute provides a mechanism for BGP speakers to convey to an adjacent AS the optimal entry point into the local AS. While BGP MEDs function correctly in many scenarios, there are a number of issues which may arise when utilizing MEDs in dynamic or complex topologies. This document discusses implementation and deployment considerations regarding BGP MEDs and provides information which implementors and network operators should be familiar with.</description>
    <dc:date>2006-01-03T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
